			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I recently decided that i want to get one of these. At lvl 25 my 2hb skill was at zero. Four levels later and it is maxed. So is peircing 1HS 2HS and 1hb. Here is what i do to train fast on a weapon. Always get a weapon with a low delay. In this case I got a Ketcha Koro Mis 7dmg 30dly from Sarnak's in Lake of ill omen. I am an ogre so i have low int. So before i get rdy to train I equip plus Int stuff. every little point of int  helps. i get mine up to 79. Then i got to a zone where groups of players around 10 lvl's higher than me are fighting and i ask if i can up my skill on their mobs. example: in Rathe Mountains)  /kneel /say I am a lvl 24 War and my 2hb skill is feeble=(  would you mind if I &quot;TRY&quot;=) to hit your hill giants that you pull to help raise my skill M'Lord? With this the lvl 34 group says &quot;sure&quot; &quot;Knock yourself out&quot; When you are hitting red con mobs that are 10 lvls higher than you with a low delay weapon and good int  your weapon skill will go up very fast. My 2hb skill went up 4 times on one hill giant. There are a few precautions. Do not hit there mob while it is incomming. Wait till it is stopped and has taken some dmg and been taunted. You never hit the taunt button. NEVER.  the amount of dmg you do will be soo small you will not agro the mob on you and you get free skill points fast. Without risking your neck by using a crapy weapon with fast delay on a mob that is blue or even to you and getting your butt kicked=)<BR>
<BR>
MEMASHU lvl 29 Ogre Warrior<BR>
