				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Aaaaaaaaaaah yes.  Thought the 2HB skill was underused and was pretty darn sure there was a decent weapon out there somewhere.  <BR>
<BR>
I've always wondered why any warrior would allow himself to become a one (or two) trick pony and ignore piercing and 2HB.  We have zero flexibility with magic.  Seems to me to be just good sense to develop maximum flexibility with weapon skills.<BR>
<BR>
&lt;chuckle&gt;  Why can't a shaman or cleric or any other class use this?  For the same reason a warrior can't cast spells or backstab or track or hide or sneak or feign death, or forage, or mend, or meditate, etc, etc.  There needs to be some sort of advantage to every class.  This just happens to be one for us warriors. 
